Collinder 121                 ; CMa  ; 06 54 34.1 -24 19 30; Op    ; OB   ;    57.00;   920;0.030; 7.070;* ;Omicron CMa Cl                                         ;Eggen (1981) suggests there is two groups in the area, de Zeeuw (1999) three. According to Kaltcheva & Makarov (2007), Cr 121 would be the superposition of the genuine compact Grp   discovered by Collinder (1931), which would be at an heliocentric distance of ~1kpc, and an extended, loose OB association with a large depth probably extending from ~0.5 to beyond 1kpc. Escorial 10, the westernmost agglomerate in the grouping, would be the genuine Collinder 121 cluster (Feinstein 1967).
